ratings.rComments: Really helpful course

Really unhelpful, he writes his own textbook which he requires you to buy and comes out with a new version of his book every year, even though there are almost non-existent  changes, so you he can require students to buy new ones instead of used ones. Also his lectures are painful to listen too. Unfortunately this a mandatory class for many people.

His tests aren't easy passes, but that's because he actually cares that students are learning the material. If you attend his classes and read the book, you'll get the grade you deserve. You work for it, and you learn so much. His lectures are stories, never just a recitation of boring  slides. His book is also an interesting read.

Professor Gottheil is incredibly nice, and knowledgeable about econ. That being said I had a hard time learning anything from him. I took this class as a freshmen and got a B, maybe I am just mad about it. Since then, in the other 9 Econ courses I've taken, I've only gotten A's or A+'s. My suggestion is to teach yourself the course from the book.

This was one of the best classes I took at the U of I! I didn't think I was going to be interested in Economics, but Professor Gottheil made it very interesting with his stories and examples! I found out that 100% of the proceeds from his book go directly into Josh's Fund, scholarships for nurses who preform bone marrow transplants. Amazing!!!

"I've taught this course over a thousand times but I'm always excited for the next class." Gottheil genuinely values the content and loves teaching. He explains complex concepts in very simple, real-life examples. He's personable and entertaining. His tests may be challenging because he really cares that students fully grasp the material.

Very tough professor, the lectures are difficult to follow, expecations on assignments and exams are not clear. The grades depends on ta since there are no good econ tas for his class. This old man is very hard to talk, and not approachable in office hours after all.

His lectures are extreme confusing and not organized, exams are very difficult which is really abstract and objective, TA grading harshly, he is a terrible professor and not sure why he teach Economics rather than any other subjects, not recommended.

Very boring lectures, makes you buy a book that he wrote for $275, then encourages you to pay an extra $15 to subscribe to the Wall Street Journal. I've never met a professor that makes you purchase his/her own book (usually they just give it to you in PDF). I could have learned more about macroeconomics for free at the public library.

Professor Gottheil has been my favorite economics professor thus far. Instead of teaching the typical profit driven economics course, he focuses on quality of life and pursuit of happiness. If you have the opportunity to take a 490 with him do it. You won't have to work too hard and you'll come out a better person.

Get in a small class with him - preferably a 490 where he is able to connect with students. Technically he teaches economics, but really he teaches life. Prof. Gottheil is one of the few profs on this campus who has actually changed my life. Every econ major should be required to take one of his 490s.

His lectures can be boring, but sometimes they are hilarious because he loves to tell stories. For the most part, he explains things well and he knows what he is talking about. The homework is really easy and comes straight from the book. The exams are essay format and long, but if you read the book, they are extremely easy. Highly recommend.

I don't understand how people say Gottheil is hard. This was probably one of the easiest classes I've taken in college. Test questions are 100% from the book which means you don't have to go to class. You have the answers to the quizes before you take them, you just need to memorize them. If you can't do well in this class, you don't belong here.
Very boring, off-topic lectures, and very difficult exams- almost impossible.
He is the best professor I have met!

He is a very nice man who loves what he does. I highly recommend reading the book if you take his class. He is very good at explaining with examples and although his test are not super easy you learn quite a bit. He makes big lectures feel small and interesting.

Most comments about Gotheil are not true. He is a great professor who knows his stuff about econ. I went to class everyday read his textbook and got an A. Those who say he is unfair did not put in the effort to receive a good grade. Students determined to do well have success in his class.

Macro can be an easy A. You have to be an active reader, internalizing the examples/concepts as you go so that they become common sense to you (~1 chapter/week + online homework). Go to lecture because he hints towards material that will be on exams (free response) & gives pop quizzes. My TA was great and having taken Micro in HS helped me a lot.

He isn't easy but isn't hard. If you take the time to study throughout the semester, you'll be fine. I took the make up midterm and it was easier than the other midterm. I don't knoe if this is a patern but thought i would add it.
He very smart but doesn't cover much in the class, but you need to attend in order to get the pop quiz points. Read the book and attend the lecture, and you'll do fine.
Gottheil's class is pretty straight forward.  His lectures can be learned just by reading the book, but go to the lectures for the 5 or so pop quizes to get those points.  Study vocab a lot!

Fred is a very good teacher who really knows what he's talking about, although Lectures are not mandatory, you can learn everything you need to know from the book. Read the book and some-what study and you will do fine in this class. I recommend taking Gottheil.
not helpful, too old school in teaching
He does not prepare you for his tests at all. Terrible at teaching. Makes it way harder than it needs to be. Read the book and pray for a good TA.

A good guy who clearly loves teaching econ. You have to know the book like the back of your hand if you expect to do well on tests. One midterm and a final which together comprise 70% of your grade. Doesn't help that this was an 8 am class...choose a different professor if possible.

He is why I am an economist and thinking about becoming a teacher! Great examples that make the content connect. I took the AP Micro class in HS and got a 3 on the exam so I had to take this class when I was able to pass out of my other intro classes though AP...wish I had him the first time around...now it totally makes sense
Go to lectures, discussion sessions and read textbooks. You WILL get an A.

No matter what anyone says, Prof Gottheil is an amazing teacher, and you learn a lot. If you put in the work and read the book, the class is pretty easy. He wrote the book and its very clear and helpful.

He absolutely loves teaching his classes.  The only problem is that his exams are very hard.  He has random quizzes which require attendance all semester long.  It is also required to go to discussion to learn material he doesn't teach.
I love Professor Gottheil!! What a great guy. You can tell he loves teaching. Not a hard class if you put in the effort.

Good guy.  You can tell that he is very knowledgeable about economics.  His lectures are hard to attend though, they rarely have anything to do with the textbook.  Exams are pretty straight-forward, just read the book and you should get an A.

I'm only attending his class because i'm a econ major. but, seriously, do not take his class!.Your grade depends on two exam, and his lecture has nothing to do with the exam. He takes alot about fishes and jokes a lot, but you will understand nothing from it. The worst i've ever seen. But he is a nice guy(sometimes arrogant).

HORRIBLE teacher, Went and asked him if he had any idea how I could find help for the class and he told me that it wasnt his problem and to figure it out. DO not take this class with him it is horrible and hard!

I was very intimidated by the reputation of this class. I never missed a class and studied constantly. In retrospect, I worked too hard for my A. This class will be very difficult for slackers, but is pretty easy for diligent students.

All I can remember him talking about is fish and sweaters.  He spends the whole class using crazy analogies to try to explain one topic, and I usually aren't able to understand the connection.  Theres 5 pop quizzes but I missed most of them and still got an A.  Just read the textbook thoroughly, thats all you will need to do well on the essay exams

His lectures have nothing to do with the book or what the exams cover. The exams are all essay questions, and in the past certain questions have appeared regarding sections as small as 3 sentences in the textbook. Not a fun professor.
Gottheil is really not as bad as I thought he would be... Tests r all essay questions and all u have to do is memorizing the book. Anyways, don't get scared by those posts lol

Makes you buy his new edition book every year which still has wrong information (see vocabulary pages). Just buy the aplia by itself and use the online textbook. I doubt you can even sell back the books. Final is almost half your semester grade. Classes are very dull where he usually only talks about fish and Canada.
Fred is fun for class but not for exams!!!!!!!!!!
Google the Aplia homework questions word for word. They can usually be found on yahoo answers. The lectures are pointless; read the book.

As a teacher, Gottheil was pretty bad.  You basically just need to read the textbook because that's all that will be on his essay midterm and final. Since essay tests are easy for me, I ended up with an A. However gottheil's lectures were useless but basically mandatory due to pop quizzes. All he talks about is fish.  Know the book and you'll pass.

horrible inefficient professor. rambles on about a story every class before teaching relevant economic concepts you could've learned in 10 minutes. If you read his textbook carefully then you'll be fine in the exams. a ton of people have his textbook so don't buy it new, even if he requires a newer edition. they're pretty much word for word the sam

horrible inefficient professor. rambles on about a story every class before teaching relevant economic concepts you could've learned in 10 minutes. If you read his textbook carefully then you'll be fine in the exams. a ton of people have his textbook so don't buy it new, even if he requires a newer edition. they're pretty much word for word the sam
Not very approachable, and seems not to care about the students as individuals
Terrible teaching style. Rambles about nothing.
Awful awful awful

Are some of these posts a joke? Did Gottheil have his TAs post on here? Were these people in the same class? Gottheil's wild tangents in class had little to do with the actual reading and the tests were just book memorization. This was by far the worst class I ever had to take, and it was supposed to be an elective. Very unorganized.
Nice guy. He tries. People just don't understand
He's awesome. Funny and creative in his lectures. He goes over the questions before the midterm and the final. Overall easy, as long as you go to class and read the textbook

The class itself was easy. I never went to lecture and aced the midterm. I'm assuming I'll do well on the final as well just because I've done well on all of the homework. The TA's suck though - none of them are American so they are very hard to understand, but that's not Gottheil's fault. Overall, easy class. You just have to read the book!

Gottheil is extremely boring and his class is neither fair nor organized. A large section of the students received the midterm and answers via email from their TAs in advance! Another time the TAs miscalculated the size the class and ran short a few hundred exams. I had to wait for other students to finish to receive a test. A terrible class.

Gottheil is terrible! His lectures are really boring, and slow. He does not know how to teach a large class, and goes on tangents pretty often. His tests are hard, and focus on very small details, not to mention they're ALL short answer. I thought Econ was interesting, after taking this class i think otherwise. You've been warned...

Terrible class. He only teaches early in the morning and talks of fishes (as someone already pointed out). He plugs the textbook which is written by himself. Lectures are pointless and exams are difficult.
This class is not hard like people say... you just have to do the work.  Read the book. that's key you should get an A if u read the book. hes actually a really smart guy

This guy is awesome! By far, best and smartest teacher I've had at U of I.  It's imperative to read the textbook and in class he clarifies examples.  The midterm and final are what most of the grade is made of and they are hard and you do have to study a lot! I enjoyed lecture though, he made me like econ more and actually learn the material.

This is one of those classes you will probably remember for quite some time -- but for all the wrong reasons! Fred is a horrible teacher who doesn't have a clue how to teach a large class. As others have written, he also insists upon essay questions when M/C could have better guaged understanding of wider set of topics. You have been warned!

Gottheil is not that bad. The class isn?t hard, but study & go to class; he may give a pop-quiz. Lectures seem dull or hard to grasp, but he?s good at putting things in simple analogies. The textbook is straight-forward; read it as the class progresses. Understand the vocab and you?re good for the exams. Be optimistic, try hard, and you?ll be ok.

Horrible class.  Gotheil goes off on tangents during class about things you never need to know.  I thought I really understood economics until it came to his tests.  If you are good at essay answer tests you should definitely take this class.  If it is at all hard to recall information I suggest not to take this class.
This professor knows what he is talking about. Despite his great deal of intellect, the class was the worst I have ever taken. The final was 16 long essay questions and was 55% of your grade.

Professor Gottheil is a really nice guy.  He is actually a very intelligent man and I respect him for donating his textbook money to charity.  However, this class is absolutely horrendous. Gottheil isn't bad. Lectures are pointless & the only reason to show up is because he gives quizzes in them. Discussion is pointless don't go to it either. The class is easy. Just 1 midterm & a final. Not too hard because it's all short answer questions. He also curves the class a letter grade. Just buy, read,& learn from his book & you're good.

Terrible lecturer. Tells bad stories with too much detail that has nothing to do with the topics. Read the book and you will do okay on the tests, which are short answer. Funny how he was not able to cover economics of exchange rate in the end because of his long, monotonous stories that help little in furthering the understanding of the topic at hand but a lot in distracting you from  the lecture. Gotheil is aloof and unhelpful as well but succeeds completely in making a very interesting subject extremely dull.

I don't understand why everyone badmouths this guy so much. His class is easy. Midterm and final are short essay questions, pretty much one from each chapter, and very predictable. the thing that makes this class so hard is not gottheil, it is the TAs. none of them care very much, and to be honest, their might be one that speaks clear english each semester. gottheil is a good professor. he knows a lot about the subject and uses useful examples in the text and in class. read the book, do the vocab words, and youll do fine.

Not interested in teaching at all. Only reason he seems to drag himself to work is that by doing so he does a very good business of selling each semester 2000 plus books that he wrote himself. Terrible class, none of the TAs spoke english, and Fred is one of the hardest graders ever. But there is not that much work to do.

I do not understand why so many people think Gottheil is a bad professor.  His lectures may be boring, but if you pay attention in them he goes over exactly what will be on the exams.  Just keep up with your reading and you will have an easy A.
Lectures were not helpful...at all

Sure, there is a book available but this is no University of Phoenix. It is one thing if a professor is not able to get his point across. It is quite another if he is not willing to try at all. I am sorry but when I am paying 20k+ for college, I expect my professors to be WILLING AND ABLE to teach. A disappointing professor thorough and thorough.

The class is not that difficult if you just read the book.  You don't have to go to lecture (although there are pop quizzes), but go to the TA sessions because they just review what he went over in lecture.  If you memorize definitions and graphs, the class isn't that difficult.

I freaked out because I thought he was going to be extremely difficult. Upon taking the course I found out that he was pretty easy. just remember all the vocabs, and you WILL get an A period

I am warning you under any circumstance.. try not to get this professor. You literally need to memorize the text book and even then its impossible. The final was worth 55% of our grade. This class will pull ur GPA down so far u'll probably cry. Avoid at all costs

Gottheil is infamous on U of I's campus as the WORST professor here. His tests are impossibly hard, a reason why his teaching career has been under review by the University for years. For a 100 level class, it will feel like a 400. Gottheil is a joke, do anything you can to avoid him.

Most boring and meaningless class ever! Attending class is only for the pop-quiz. There will be five, each counts for 1%. Make sure you are there in the last 10 minutes. I fail to understand why so many people hate Gottheil. He has been an inspiration to me not only for his out-of-the-box, interesting lesssons, but also for the passion with which he teaches everyday. terrible.  obviously a very smart guy, but can't teach.  exams are impossible.  lecture was useless.

Great teacher that actually teaches econ and how it is used in the real world. Doesnt just put notes on a board rather has interesting lectures. He is tough but it's a good class and challenges you.

Gottheil's 102 is the reason I became an Econ major. He is an outstanding teacher for those who want more than just a blow off class. He doesn't rehash what is in the book. He expects you to read it on your own. And know it. He is EXTREMELY approachable. Use his office hours. Use him well.
he was really hard and didn't explain anything. i recommend you don't take this class, its hard and you don't learn anything.

idk y he gets such a bad rep. hes a good teacher, and the class is not very difficult if you actually go and take good notes. tests are pretty hard, they make you apply what you've learned to real world problems, which can be difficult. if you want to actually learn economics, take gottheil.

Lectures and not very interesting. Most of it is just repeated from the text, so you don't have to attend. His pop quizzes are irritating as you have to attend the lectures since you don't know when he would give them. Haven't met him, so don't know how approachable he is during his office hours.
i liked him
